- Stopped proccesses keep running after sending them SIGSTOP (-19), and they disappear from the job list.
- Ctrl-c signal generates a "waitpid failed: Interrupted system call".
- Ctrl-z signal doesnt stop the proccess, or keeps running in the foreground.
- Double ctrl-z's exit the smash.
- Doing "quit kill" while there are proccesses that are STOPPED, generates a "(5 sec passed) Sending SIGKILL... Done" message and exits the smash.
